President Obama has announced his intent to nominate David "Mas" Masumoto as a member of the National Council on the Arts and Polly Trottenberg as the Under Secretary for Policy at the Department of Transportation. Masumoto is an organic peach and grape farmer, author, and columnist for The Fresno Bee. He has received several writing awards and serves on various boards, including the James Irvine Foundation and the Public Policy Institute of California. Trottenberg is currently the Assistant Secretary for Transportation Policy at the Department of Transportation. She has previously held positions in the U.S. Senate and worked at the Port Authority of New York and New Jersey.